I'll get more from the car.


250
00:33:16.992 --> 00:33:20.370
- Where did she go?
- She's like an elevator!


251
00:35:10.606 --> 00:35:14.943
You're everything, Sylvia.
You know that?


252
00:35:18.822 --> 00:35:22.534
The first woman
on the first day of creation.


253
00:35:23.285 --> 00:35:26.454
You're mother, sister,
lover, friend,


254
00:35:26.747 --> 00:35:29.624
angel, devil, earth, home.

255
00:35:29.792 --> 00:35:32.794
That's what you are: home.

256
00:35:38.842 --> 00:35:41.427
Why did you come here?

257
00:35:42.096 --> 00:35:44.472
Go back to America, please.

258
00:35:44.640 --> 00:35:47.141
What will I do now?

259
00:36:03.492 --> 00:36:06.619
Our Robert is a painter too.
Bravo!


260
00:36:07.538 --> 00:36:10.206
I absolutely must see you
and talk to you.


261
00:36:30.853 --> 00:36:34.856
- Who is that idiot?
- Frankie Stout, a divine actor.


262
00:37:06.513 --> 00:37:08.056
Please.

263
00:37:27.910 --> 00:37:31.704
- Will you excuse me a moment?
- Go on, sweetheart.


264
00:37:33.415 --> 00:37:35.750
He's dancing with the lady.

265
00:39:10.012 --> 00:39:11.679
Hi, darling.

266
00:39:21.732 --> 00:39:23.608
He's a good dancer.

267
00:39:24.026 --> 00:39:25.943
Really great.

268
00:39:27.362 --> 00:39:29.655
Are you making a banana flambé?

269
00:39:29.907 --> 00:39:32.867
- The lady's shoes.
- Give them here.


270
00:39:33.035 --> 00:39:36.037
- I found them on...
- That's fine, thank you.


271
00:39:36.205 --> 00:39:39.207
Excuse me. One moment.

272
00:40:04.066 --> 00:40:05.650
What do you want?

273
00:42:27.542 --> 00:42:31.170
Bravo, Frankie!
You were wonderful!


274
00:42:34.132 --> 00:42:35.883
You were wonderful!

275
00:42:38.971 --> 00:42:41.931
What class, madame!
What style!


276
00:42:42.224 --> 00:42:44.934
That was dangerous but beautiful!

277
00:42:45.060 --> 00:42:46.811
Thank you, sir.

278
00:42:50.399 --> 00:42:52.775
Marcello,
give me the champagne.


279
00:43:44.828 --> 00:43:48.664
I'll bring her back immediately.

280
00:43:48.832 --> 00:43:51.417
Give me the shoes.
I'll be right back.


281
00:43:51.626 --> 00:43:54.670
- Why's she so upset?
- Stay here. I'll handle it.


282
00:43:55.589 --> 00:43:57.173
Here she is!

283
00:43:58.258 --> 00:44:00.092
Sylvia, your shoes.

284
00:44:00.343 --> 00:44:02.845
- Marcello, what happened?
- Nothing. Go away.


285
00:44:07.934 --> 00:44:09.852
Great idea, Marcello.

286
00:44:17.652 --> 00:44:20.446
Paparazzo, get out!

287
00:44:20.572 --> 00:44:23.824
It'll be a worldwide scoop.
I'll give you 50 percent.


288
00:44:23.992 --> 00:44:27.161
Screw your 50 percent!
Beat it!


289
00:44:31.583 --> 00:44:34.877
Get lost!
- Where are you going?


290
00:44:36.546 --> 00:44:39.006
Hurry, follow them!

291
00:44:59.027 --> 00:45:01.028
We've lost them.

292
00:45:08.578 --> 00:45:10.621
Yes... of course.

293
00:46:19.774 --> 00:46:21.400
What is it?

294
00:46:48.845 --> 00:46:50.971
It's full of holes there.

295
00:47:09.324 --> 00:47:11.325
We'd better go now.

296
00:47:20.210 --> 00:47:24.338
Sergio will be back on the 12th.
This is his mother.


297
00:47:24.506 --> 00:47:28.634
- Do you have the key to his place?
- No, he takes it with him.


298
00:47:28.760 --> 00:47:31.303
I'm his mother.
Is this about work?


299
00:47:31.805 --> 00:47:34.682
Yes, it's about work.

300
00:47:36.559 --> 00:47:39.478
I'll call on the 12th.
It doesn't matter.


301
00:47:39.646 --> 00:47:41.897
Sorry, ma'am. Good night.

302
00:47:45.110 --> 00:47:48.362
Excuse me, isn't that
the American actress?


303
00:47:48.571 --> 00:47:49.655
Yes.

304
00:47:49.823 --> 00:47:51.824
- She's so beautiful!
- Good night.


305
00:48:02.377 --> 00:48:06.547
I can't take you to my place.
That crazy woman's there.


306
00:48:06.715 --> 00:48:09.883
She wouldn't understand.
- Un-der-stand?


307
00:48:11.177 --> 00:48:13.595
Wait, I have an idea.

308
00:48:16.599 --> 00:48:19.393
Miss, a phone call for you.

309
00:48:22.564 --> 00:48:26.567
Marcello! Sure you don't have
the wrong number?


310
00:48:27.068 --> 00:48:29.820
Maddalena, may I bring
someone there?


311
00:48:30.071 --> 00:48:33.365
- "Someone"?
- Who calls at this hour?


312
00:48:33.992 --> 00:48:38.620
Just someone.
You're not alone?


313
00:48:39.414 --> 00:48:42.041
I'm playing cards with my father.

314
00:48:44.210 --> 00:48:45.878
Ah, your father's there.

315
00:48:46.254 --> 00:48:47.796
Tell me...

316
00:48:49.257 --> 00:48:50.924
what is it you want?

317
00:48:51.634 --> 00:48:54.928
Nothing. I'll call you soon.
Good night.


318
00:49:10.070 --> 00:49:12.404
Sylvia, what are you doing?

319
00:49:21.748 --> 00:49:24.750
Where would I find milk
at this hour?


320
00:49:28.630 --> 00:49:30.130
Sylvia, come on.

321
00:49:30.298 --> 00:49:34.134
Where are you taking that cat?
Rome is full of cats. If we start...


322
00:49:34.302 --> 00:49:35.677
Stop.

323
00:49:36.304 --> 00:49:37.805
Come on.

324
00:49:38.473 --> 00:49:42.309
You'll never find milk.
Wait in the car. I'll go.


325
00:49:44.020 --> 00:49:45.479
I'll go.

326
00:49:46.481 --> 00:49:47.815
Go on.

327
00:49:56.825 --> 00:49:59.660
Excuse me,
where can I buy some milk?


328
00:50:00.703 --> 00:50:02.454
Okay, never mind.

329
00:51:38.635 --> 00:51:41.303
Yes, Sylvia, I'm coming too.

330
00:51:42.388 --> 00:51:43.889
I'm coming too.

331
00:51:48.728 --> 00:51:51.730
She's right.
I've had it all wrong.


332
00:51:52.440 --> 00:51:54.316
We've all had it wrong.

333
00:52:08.039 --> 00:52:10.207
Sylvia, who are you?

334
00:52:47.495 --> 00:52:49.162
Turn his head.

335
00:52:54.002 --> 00:52:56.461
To think this guy played Tarzan.

336
00:52:56.588 --> 00:52:58.463
Turn his head back.

337
00:53:04.304 --> 00:53:06.888
I'll get an over-the-mirror shot.

338
00:53:07.515 --> 00:53:10.392
And I'll get one of you
taking his picture.


339
00:53:12.645 --> 00:53:14.354
Here's Marcello!

340
00:53:17.859 --> 00:53:19.818
Boys, don't start now.

341
00:53:20.028 --> 00:53:21.320
Wake up!

342
00:53:30.121 --> 00:53:32.998
Marcello, give us all the details.

343
00:53:33.625 --> 00:53:37.294
- Do me a favor and go away.
- I have to work!


344
00:53:37.420 --> 00:53:39.046
Enough!

345
00:53:40.048 --> 00:53:43.216
Marcello,
why are your clothes all wet?


346
00:53:43.384 --> 00:53:44.885
I don't know!

347
00:53:50.808 --> 00:53:53.226
There's gonna be a fight.

348
00:54:19.837 --> 00:54:21.505
Follow her, Mr. Robert!

349
00:54:23.591 --> 00:54:25.592
This isn't over yet.

350
00:54:29.597 --> 00:54:32.933
- Here he is, Marcello.
- Hit him first.


351
00:54:47.281 --> 00:54:49.783
Marcello, raise your head a bit.

352
00:54:49.951 --> 00:54:52.035
He's walking away!
Mr. Robert!


353
00:55:00.128 --> 00:55:02.462
Marcello, that's done.
What now?


354
00:55:03.506 --> 00:55:06.633
Put the horse on the table
and her on the ground.


355
00:55:13.725 --> 00:55:15.142
I'll be right back.

356
00:55:15.268 --> 00:55:18.437
So can I pick you up
at 8:00 tonight?


357
00:55:18.563 --> 00:55:20.480
You're so vain!

358
00:55:20.648 --> 00:55:23.358
I'm not vain. I'm working.

359
00:55:36.289 --> 00:55:37.789
Steiner!

360
00:55:39.083 --> 00:55:42.043
I thought I saw you come in here.
How are you?


361
00:55:42.170 --> 00:55:46.006
What are you doing here?
- It's so good to see you again.


362
00:55:48.509 --> 00:55:51.011
This is like my second home.

363
00:55:51.846 --> 00:55:56.892
Father Franz finally found this book
I've been looking for forever.


364
00:55:57.059 --> 00:55:59.644
An old Sanskrit grammar.

365
00:56:01.522 --> 00:56:05.358
It's been so long!
How's your book going?


366
00:56:05.902 --> 00:56:09.654
Oh... it's coming along.
I've finished gathering material.


367
00:56:09.822 --> 00:56:12.407
I thought I'd ask you to read it.

368
00:56:12.533 --> 00:56:15.160
And you?
- I read your last article.


369
00:56:15.328 --> 00:56:17.537
I liked it very much.

370
00:56:19.207 --> 00:56:22.000
Why? It was very good.

371
00:56:23.169 --> 00:56:28.548
It was clear and passionate...
your best qualities.


372
00:56:28.716 --> 00:56:31.885
The ones you insist
on trying to hide.


373
00:56:32.094 --> 00:56:34.846
I don't think
I even know how to write.


374
00:56:34.972 --> 00:56:38.725
I live nearby. Why don't you
come by some evening?


375
00:56:40.144 --> 00:56:43.522
Can you stay five more minutes?
- Of course.


376
00:56:45.858 --> 00:56:48.777
- Father, may I bring a friend up?
- Certainly.


377
00:56:49.028 --> 00:56:52.113
- We're not disturbing you?
- Not at all.


378
00:56:52.240 --> 00:56:56.827
As you see,
these priests don't fear the devil.


379
00:56:57.995 --> 00:57:00.455
They even let me play the organ.

380
00:57:01.916 --> 00:57:04.417
Just don't make a racket, okay?

381
00:57:04.544 --> 00:57:07.587
Don't worry.
Maybe some jazz, that's all.


382
00:57:07.755 --> 00:57:11.591
Couldn't we close the church?
- Jazz is fine by me.


383
00:57:13.928 --> 00:57:16.847
Sorry, I won't do that again.

384
00:57:17.765 --> 00:57:20.225
You want to try?

385
00:57:27.191 --> 00:57:29.734
Sounds we're no longer
used to hearing.


386
00:57:30.653 --> 00:57:34.573
Like a mysterious voice
from deep within the earth.


387
00:57:35.032 --> 00:57:38.034
What do you want to hear?
- You choose.


388
00:58:55.237 --> 00:58:58.406
Where did they say it was?

389
00:58:58.532 --> 00:59:03.328
Hey, Paparazzo!
- They said at the 47th kilometer.


390
00:59:06.582 --> 00:59:09.417
I don't want an egg right now!

391
00:59:09.585 --> 00:59:11.252
I don't want it!
- Eat.


392
00:59:13.756 --> 00:59:15.590
And chew slowly.

393
00:59:15.967 --> 00:59:20.762
We should have come yesterday.
It'll be full of photographers.


394
00:59:21.389 --> 00:59:23.932
Is there any coffee left?

395
00:59:24.058 --> 00:59:26.559
The little that's left
is for Marcello.


396
00:59:27.395 --> 00:59:29.396
I don't want a banana!

397
00:59:30.022 --> 00:59:32.941
I don't want it!
- Eat it.


398
00:59:36.153 --> 00:59:38.029
And chew slowly.

399
00:59:47.081 --> 00:59:50.083
- The Madonna's children?
- Yes.


400
00:59:50.418 --> 00:59:55.130
- Where's the field of miracles?
- That way.


401
01:00:14.608 --> 01:00:17.444
You'd better wait here.
There's too much commotion.


402
01:00:21.449 --> 01:00:23.700
Norman.

403
01:00:24.326 --> 01:00:25.994
Don't go anywhere.

404
01:00:30.958 --> 01:00:33.585
Norman, where are the kids?

405
01:00:33.753 --> 01:00:36.254
Locked up in the police station.

406
01:00:36.756 --> 01:00:40.133
Take me with you.
I'll tell you what the communists did.


407
01:00:40.301 --> 01:00:43.178
- Is that the miracle tree?
- Down at the end.


408
01:00:46.348 --> 01:00:49.309
Damn the police!
Damn the police!


409
01:01:01.155 --> 01:01:05.909
You have no right
to detain those children!


410
01:01:06.160 --> 01:01:09.162
- Everyone's upstairs.
- Let's go in.


411
01:01:14.001 --> 01:01:15.502
Come on!

412
01:01:18.923 --> 01:01:20.799
Which way?
- In there.


413
01:01:21.550 --> 01:01:24.177
- Ma'am, where are the children?
- I don't know.


414
01:01:24.345 --> 01:01:26.638
- And the sergeant?
- Who knows?


415
01:01:32.394 --> 01:01:35.688
What about the 500 lira
the reporter gave you?


416
01:01:35.815 --> 01:01:40.360
- The father and mother!
- Can I go home, inspector?


417
01:01:43.656 --> 01:01:46.950
My back hurts, and I'm cold.

418
01:01:47.076 --> 01:01:49.536
Yes, it's like winter here.

419
01:01:52.915 --> 01:01:55.458
Look over there.

420
01:01:55.584 --> 01:01:57.627
That's good.

421
01:02:01.382 --> 01:02:05.385
- Now stand here.
- The grandfather's here too!


422
01:02:05.553 --> 01:02:08.847
You must be a very happy mother.
What are their names?


423
01:02:09.014 --> 01:02:11.057
Dario and Maria.

424
01:02:11.183 --> 01:02:13.977
Great names.
That's right, cry!


425
01:02:14.270 --> 01:02:18.398
It's a miracle.
The Madonna remembers everyone.


426
01:02:18.774 --> 01:02:21.484
Is this good?
- Perfect!


427
01:02:23.028 --> 01:02:25.405
- A cigar.
- Sing first.


428
01:02:30.077 --> 01:02:33.037
- So it's not a miracle?
- I don't believe so.


429
01:02:33.205 --> 01:02:35.665
The Lord can perform
miracles anywhere,


430
01:02:35.791 --> 01:02:37.917
often among the most destitute,

431
01:02:38.085 --> 01:02:40.712
but they're very rare events.
- Couldn't this be one?


432
01:02:40.880 --> 01:02:43.089
No, those children are lying.

433
01:02:43.257 --> 01:02:48.344
Seeing the Madonna changes a person.
They don't try to profit from it.


434
01:02:48.470 --> 01:02:52.765
Miracles occur
in prayer and silence,


435
01:02:52.933 --> 01:02:54.684
not in all this hubbub!

436
01:02:55.144 --> 01:02:59.272
On your way to school,
whom did you see beside the tree?


437
01:02:59.398 --> 01:03:02.233
- The Madonna.
- Who saw her first?


438
01:03:02.359 --> 01:03:03.484
- Me!
- Me!


439
01:03:03.652 --> 01:03:05.445
At the same time?

440
01:03:05.571 --> 01:03:07.530
No, he saw her first.

441
01:03:07.656 --> 01:03:09.991
- Then what happened?
- I'm their uncle.


442
01:03:10.117 --> 01:03:13.494
We knelt down,
and the Madonna smiled at us.


443
01:03:13.621 --> 01:03:16.122
Her feet didn't even touch
the ground.


444
01:03:16.290 --> 01:03:18.917
How did you know
it was the Madonna?


445
01:03:19.418 --> 01:03:22.086
They don't want to believe it.

446
01:03:22.630 --> 01:03:25.131
You mean you think
it really was her?


447
01:03:25.299 --> 01:03:27.342
It doesn't matter if it was or not.

448
01:03:28.302 --> 01:03:31.763
What do you mean?
Why do you say that?


449
01:03:31.889 --> 01:03:33.806
It doesn't matter.

450
01:03:33.974 --> 01:03:37.060
Your country
is a land of ancient beliefs,


451
01:03:37.186 --> 01:03:39.437
filled with supernatural forces,

452
01:03:39.563 --> 01:03:41.981
so everyone feels their influence.

453
01:03:42.107 --> 01:03:45.568
Besides, he who looks for God
finds him wherever he wants.


454
01:03:45.694 --> 01:03:47.695
Did you come for a miracle too?

455
01:03:48.113 --> 01:03:50.490
No, I'm here with my fiancé.

456
01:03:50.658 --> 01:03:53.326
He's a journalist on assignment.

457
01:03:54.453 --> 01:03:59.082
All these people and all this shouting
frighten me a little.


458
01:03:59.458 --> 01:04:04.003
Stand there. Don't look
at the camera, and don't laugh.


459
01:04:04.380 --> 01:04:07.131
Higher. Keep going.

460
01:04:07.508 --> 01:04:11.135
No, I was wrong.
Come down.


461
01:04:11.595 --> 01:04:14.013
Let's work out
how to frame the children.


462
01:04:14.139 --> 01:04:16.683
Remember: Children are short.

463
01:04:16.850 --> 01:04:19.519
Am I in the shot?

464
01:04:19.687 --> 01:04:22.522
Come on, everyone.
Quickly!


465
01:04:22.982 --> 01:04:24.524
Hurry, please!

466
01:04:25.359 --> 01:04:28.569
- There's my fiancé.
- Yes, go join him.


467
01:04:28.696 --> 01:04:30.613
Excuse me a moment.

468
01:04:31.532 --> 01:04:33.491
Ready? Action!

469
01:04:34.118 --> 01:04:39.038
Louder!
All of you have to pray!


470
01:04:43.210 --> 01:04:46.879
It's 7:00 now.
We'll start again in two hours.


471
01:04:47.089 --> 01:04:50.341
Get something to eat.
See you tonight.


472
01:04:50.509 --> 01:04:52.093
Enjoy your dinner!

473
01:05:03.355 --> 01:05:07.775
Holy Madonna,
please heal my little girl.


474
01:05:08.068 --> 01:05:11.612
Grant me this miracle.
I ask you with all my soul.


475
01:05:25.085 --> 01:05:27.045
Don't worry, my darling.

476
01:05:27.171 --> 01:05:30.465
The Madonna hears us.
She is good.


477
01:06:04.124 --> 01:06:08.920
A huge crowd has gathered
in this remote and deserted region.


478
01:06:09.296 --> 01:06:12.173
Many are believers.
Others are just curious.


479
01:06:12.341 --> 01:06:15.510
Among the latter
are reporters and photographers


480
01:06:15.761 --> 01:06:18.763
from newspapers
from all over the world.


481
01:06:19.390 --> 01:06:22.266
An endless line of cars
has been arriving.


482
01:06:22.559 --> 01:06:27.397
It's humid, but the sky is clear
after all the rain.


483
01:06:27.523 --> 01:06:30.650
The two children
are still in police custody,


484
01:06:30.859 --> 01:06:33.820
with no further word
from Rome regarding them.


485
01:06:33.987 --> 01:06:37.490
Let's speak
to the children's uncle now.


486
01:06:37.783 --> 01:06:41.744
When did they first see the...

487
01:06:42.663 --> 01:06:44.455
the miracle?

488
01:06:44.706 --> 01:06:48.918
My niece and nephew first saw
the holy image of the Madonna


489
01:06:49.044 --> 01:06:50.837
on March 15 of...

490
01:06:52.214 --> 01:06:53.673
next year.

491
01:06:53.841 --> 01:06:56.175
- You mean this year.
- This year.


492
01:06:56.844 --> 01:07:01.180
They're releasing the children.
Permission came from Rome.


493
01:07:01.348 --> 01:07:03.558
They're coming!
They've released them!


494
01:07:05.561 --> 01:07:09.230
You stay here. Good evening.
I'll be right back.


495
01:07:09.398 --> 01:07:11.566
- Where are you going?
- Up there.


496
01:07:11.692 --> 01:07:15.695
- I'll come with you.
- No, stay here with the lady.


497
01:07:20.617 --> 01:07:22.118
Wait here.

498
01:07:37.050 --> 01:07:38.968
Marcello, come down!

499
01:07:39.386 --> 01:07:41.846
I just got up here! Relax!

500
01:07:46.143 --> 01:07:48.561
Shall I come up too?

501
01:08:07.247 --> 01:08:10.791
Marcello,
why have you changed so much?


502
01:08:11.960 --> 01:08:14.420
Why don't you love me anymore?

503
01:08:18.926 --> 01:08:21.928
Dear Madonna,
if he'd only marry me,


504
01:08:22.095 --> 01:08:25.806
I'd come here on foot
every day to thank you.


505
01:08:26.266 --> 01:08:28.601
But I don't even ask for that much.

506
01:08:28.769 --> 01:08:32.355
Just that he be mine again,
like he was once.


507
01:08:32.481 --> 01:08:35.024
Here they come!

508
01:08:35.943 --> 01:08:37.360
Here they come.

509
01:08:37.486 --> 01:08:41.113
When they get to the tree,
start filming.


510
01:09:16.400 --> 01:09:19.652
Wait till I signal you
with my handkerchief.


511
01:09:20.112 --> 01:09:24.115
How are you, sweetie?
Focus on them with the crowd behind.


512
01:09:24.241 --> 01:09:26.325
It's dark back here!

513
01:09:36.044 --> 01:09:38.379
My wife's down there too.

514
01:09:40.048 --> 01:09:43.426
Sometimes she makes me so mad,
and then other times...


515
01:09:47.889 --> 01:09:50.391
Heal me!

516
01:09:59.192 --> 01:10:01.444
Stay calm.

517
01:10:02.863 --> 01:10:04.989
One at a time.

518
01:10:11.121 --> 01:10:13.706
- It's gonna rain.
- That's dangerous.


519
01:10:22.090 --> 01:10:26.135
The lights will short-circuit!
Shut everything off!


520
01:10:27.054 --> 01:10:30.139
Turn off all generators!

521
01:10:45.614 --> 01:10:50.368
We've taken shelter in the bus
because the rain's started up again.


522
01:11:06.718 --> 01:11:08.761
The Madonna's over there!

523
01:11:24.695 --> 01:11:27.613
The children are getting up again

524
01:11:27.906 --> 01:11:30.449
and running the other way.

525
01:11:30.617 --> 01:11:32.952
They're shouting
that they see the Madonna.


526
01:11:33.120 --> 01:11:35.454
The crowd's going wild
and following them.


527
01:11:50.429 --> 01:11:54.849
Once again
they're running to a different spot.


528
01:12:12.325 --> 01:12:14.201
There she is!

529
01:12:27.549 --> 01:12:32.344
Let me through!
They'll catch pneumonia in this rain!


530
01:12:39.811 --> 01:12:43.022
Quiet! The Madonna said
to build a church here


531
01:12:43.148 --> 01:12:45.191
or she won't appear anymore.

532
01:12:45.400 --> 01:12:47.276
Good night! Go home!

533
01:14:00.392 --> 01:14:02.142
Let me go!

534
01:14:03.311 --> 01:14:06.605
- Paparazzo, stop it!
- It's a great shot.


535
01:14:06.773 --> 01:14:11.193
Let me go!
How dare you act like that!


536
01:14:11.444 --> 01:14:14.780
You're worse than hyenas!

537
01:14:14.990 --> 01:14:17.616
You have no respect for anyone!

538
01:14:29.963 --> 01:14:33.632
What are you crying for?
Where'd you leave it?


539
01:14:33.800 --> 01:14:36.302
I don't remember!

540
01:14:44.060 --> 01:14:46.270
He's dead!

541
01:14:50.150 --> 01:14:51.817
He's dead!

542
01:15:35.487 --> 01:15:38.030
Good evening.
I'm Steiner's wife.


543
01:15:38.198 --> 01:15:40.324
We've been expecting you.

544
01:15:55.382 --> 01:15:57.591
Good evening, Marcello.
How are you?


545
01:15:57.759 --> 01:15:59.885
Fine. What a lovely home!

546
01:16:00.470 --> 01:16:04.348
This must be Emma.
I've been wanting to meet you.


547
01:16:05.350 --> 01:16:07.726
Thank you for coming.
- Excuse me.


548
01:16:08.019 --> 01:16:09.436
Come here.

549
01:16:10.021 --> 01:16:12.940
- Anna, how are you?
- Did you finish your book?


550
01:16:13.066 --> 01:16:15.901
You must know Margherita's work?
- Of course.


551
01:16:16.069 --> 01:16:19.071
And you didn't even come
to my exhibition!


552
01:16:19.572 --> 01:16:24.952
She loves your writing,
but she doesn't speak any Italian.


553
01:16:25.120 --> 01:16:28.580
She did say you're very handsome.
- She's right.


554
01:16:31.084 --> 01:16:33.877
Odd as it sounds,
I feel I know you well.


555
01:16:34.713 --> 01:16:38.757
The day you realize you love Marcello
more than he loves himself...


556
01:16:40.635 --> 01:16:42.720
you'll be happy.

557
01:16:47.392 --> 01:16:51.270
I've always said:
The only real women are from the Orient.


558
01:16:51.688 --> 01:16:55.441
After all, where was Eve?
In the Garden of Eden.


559
01:16:55.775 --> 01:16:58.777
Where was the Garden of Eden?
In the Orient.


560
01:16:58.945 --> 01:17:02.781
There love is...
- So why did you marry me?


561
01:17:02.949 --> 01:17:05.034
I made a big mistake!

562
01:17:05.160 --> 01:17:07.578
Mysterious, maternal...

563
01:17:07.704 --> 01:17:09.663
lover and daughter in one.

564
01:17:09.789 --> 01:17:12.750
She huddles at your feet

565
01:17:12.876 --> 01:17:14.877
like a love-struck little tiger.

566
01:17:15.003 --> 01:17:19.381
Why doesn't he just go
and live there?


567
01:17:19.507 --> 01:17:21.925
Will you introduce me to Emma?
- Of course.


568
01:17:22.302 --> 01:17:27.097
What a lovely face!
Listen, hold on tight to this guy.


569
01:17:27.265 --> 01:17:30.934
For his sake, I mean.

570
01:17:31.061 --> 01:17:34.772
The Oriental woman submits
both in spirit


571
01:17:34.898 --> 01:17:36.398
and flesh.

572
01:17:36.524 --> 01:17:40.986
May I introduce Marcello
and his fiancée, Emma?


573
01:17:41.154 --> 01:17:44.323
Pleased to meet you.
I agree with your concept of women.


574
01:17:44.949 --> 01:17:48.660
The Oriental woman
has much to teach us,


575
01:17:48.787 --> 01:17:50.788
because she has remained
close to nature,


576
01:17:50.955 --> 01:17:54.083
a nature conquered
after centuries of civilization.


577
01:17:54.501 --> 01:17:58.337
What use is civilization to you?
- What's it to you?


578
01:17:58.505 --> 01:18:01.548
You don't know
how to make love anymore.


579
01:18:01.716 --> 01:18:03.884
Speak for yourself.

580
01:18:04.219 --> 01:18:05.844
- Something to drink?
- Yes, please.


581
01:18:06.012 --> 01:18:08.013
I'm jealous of you.

582
01:18:08.139 --> 01:18:11.183
I've read all your stories
from around the world.


583
01:18:11.351 --> 01:18:14.353
I'd like to travel too

584
01:18:14.479 --> 01:18:17.356
and meet women of all races.

585
01:18:17.524 --> 01:18:21.068
I'd like to have children
of every color: red, yellow.


586
01:18:21.236 --> 01:18:25.197
Like a bouquet of flowers.
- Is that all you can say?


587
01:18:25.365 --> 01:18:28.158
You must have incredible memories.

588
01:18:28.284 --> 01:18:31.161
At my age,
memories aren't enough.


589
01:18:31.287 --> 01:18:33.372
I have plans!

590
01:18:33.540 --> 01:18:36.583
What a splendid creature!
Are you his fiancée?


591
01:18:36.751 --> 01:18:39.044
- Yes.
- You must be from the south.


592
01:18:39.379 --> 01:18:41.380
What an extraordinary character.

593
01:18:41.548 --> 01:18:44.341
He's written dozens
of important books,


594
01:18:44.634 --> 01:18:47.261
yet he's maintained
a childlike candor.


595
01:18:47.387 --> 01:18:50.681
I wonder how he can be
so optimistic.


596
01:18:51.599 --> 01:18:54.768
I always watch him
with amazement.


597
01:18:55.061 --> 01:18:57.980
Sometimes I wonder if I envy him.

598
01:18:58.106 --> 01:19:01.567
I see you have
a beautiful Morandi.


599
01:19:01.901 --> 01:19:04.778
Yes, he's my favorite painter.

600
01:19:05.029 --> 01:19:07.739
His subjects are immersed
in a dreamlike light,


601
01:19:07.907 --> 01:19:12.035
yet painted with such detachment,
precision, and rigor


602
01:19:12.745 --> 01:19:14.997
that you could almost touch them.

603
01:19:15.123 --> 01:19:18.625
It's an art
where nothing is coincidental.


604
01:19:18.751 --> 01:19:21.587
Steiner says you have two loves,

605
01:19:21.754 --> 01:19:24.089
and you don't know which to choose:

606
01:19:24.424 --> 01:19:26.717
journalism or literature.

607
01:19:26.843 --> 01:19:29.011
Beware of prisons!

608
01:19:29.137 --> 01:19:32.097
Remain free, available.
Like me.


609
01:19:33.099 --> 01:19:36.643
Never marry anything.
Never choose.


610
01:19:37.020 --> 01:19:39.605
Even in love,
it's better to be chosen.


611
01:19:44.027 --> 01:19:47.154
I read your poems
when I thought of writing poetry.


612
01:19:47.280 --> 01:19:49.406
I like them.
They're powerful, precise.


613
01:19:49.657 --> 01:19:51.450
It's not like a woman's writing.

614
01:19:51.618 --> 01:19:54.119
What would you know
about women?


615
01:19:54.704 --> 01:19:58.457
I prefer that type of art.
We'll need it in the future.


616
01:19:58.666 --> 01:20:01.668
Art that's clear
and free of rhetoric,


617
01:20:01.794 --> 01:20:04.796
that doesn't lie or flatter.

618
01:20:05.381 --> 01:20:09.968
I don't like the work I do now,
but I often think about tomorrow.


619
01:20:10.178 --> 01:20:14.890
We must all think of tomorrow
but without forgetting to live today.


620
01:20:15.058 --> 01:20:20.687
I believe if we live
with an intense fullness of spirit,


621
01:20:20.980 --> 01:20:23.065
every moment counts
as a whole year,


622
01:20:23.191 --> 01:20:26.026
and every year
we get five years younger!


623
01:20:30.114 --> 01:20:32.866
Iris, you're a prophet tonight.

624
01:20:32.992 --> 01:20:35.661
An alcoholic prophet!

625
01:20:37.830 --> 01:20:40.832
My friends, you think
too much about the future.


626
01:20:41.000 --> 01:20:44.044
But you seem so different.

627
01:20:44.170 --> 01:20:45.671
What do you do?

628
01:20:45.797 --> 01:20:49.007
I mean,
what do you like to do most?


629
01:20:50.301 --> 01:20:52.552
I don't know. You?

630
01:20:53.221 --> 01:20:56.556
I like the three great escapes:

631
01:20:56.683 --> 01:20:59.726
smoking, drinking, and bed.

632
01:20:59.978 --> 01:21:01.979
So this is your wisdom?

633
01:21:02.105 --> 01:21:04.690
You read my work
but understand nothing.


634
01:21:05.275 --> 01:21:07.526
You're the true primitive,

635
01:21:07.694 --> 01:21:10.362
primitive like a gothic spire.

636
01:21:10.530 --> 01:21:15.659
You're so tall that no voices
can reach you up there.


637
01:21:15.785 --> 01:21:18.203
Really? If you could see
my real height,


638
01:21:18.371 --> 01:21:20.747
you'd see I'm no taller than this.

639
01:21:30.550 --> 01:21:32.884
...primitive like a gothic spire.

640
01:21:33.052 --> 01:21:37.848
You're so tall that no voices
can reach you up there.


641
01:21:38.016 --> 01:21:40.851
Really? If you could see
my real height,


642
01:21:40.977 --> 01:21:43.520
you'd see I'm no taller than this.

643
01:21:48.234 --> 01:21:51.987
This is an old recording.
I'll turn it off.


644
01:21:52.238 --> 01:21:55.073
What is it?
Why can't we hear it?


645
01:21:55.450 --> 01:21:58.618
I don't want to bore you.
They're just meaningless sounds.


646
01:21:58.745 --> 01:22:01.496
They're nature sounds he recorded.

647
01:22:01.622 --> 01:22:05.042
Please tell him to play it.
Please.


648
01:22:05.543 --> 01:22:08.587
Why record them
if they're of no interest?


649
01:22:08.755 --> 01:22:10.797
I thought they were beautiful.

650
01:22:10.923 --> 01:22:12.841
You really want to hear them?
- Yes!


651
01:22:12.967 --> 01:22:15.302
I've heard them.
They're very stimulating.


652
01:22:15.595 --> 01:22:17.095
As you wish.

653
01:22:42.955 --> 01:22:44.623
Birds.

654
01:22:47.377 --> 01:22:49.586
That's exactly how they sound.

655
01:22:56.469 --> 01:22:57.761
A forest.

656
01:23:09.107 --> 01:23:11.775
What are you two doing here?

657
01:23:12.276 --> 01:23:15.278
Why are you out of bed?
- Excuse me.


658
01:23:15.696 --> 01:23:18.865
You'll catch cold
in those bare feet!


659
01:23:19.158 --> 01:23:21.451
Your storm woke him up.

660
01:23:25.123 --> 01:23:29.167
- Did you want one more kiss?
- Daddy bighead!


661
01:23:29.335 --> 01:23:31.670
Daddy bighead!
How dare you!


662
01:23:31.838 --> 01:23:34.923
Now everyone knows.
Daddy has a big head.


663
01:23:35.258 --> 01:23:37.342
What lovely children!

664
01:23:38.344 --> 01:23:41.721
He has such intelligent eyes!
- It's true.


665
01:23:42.181 --> 01:23:45.684
If he hears something interesting,
first he thinks about it


666
01:23:45.852 --> 01:23:50.188
with a serious little face,
and then he laughs cheerfully.


667
01:23:51.357 --> 01:23:54.985
If you give him a flower,
first he examines it,


668
01:23:55.194 --> 01:23:58.321
and then he laughs
because he understands it's beautiful.


669
01:23:58.489 --> 01:24:01.741
The same way you smile
when you listen to nice music.


670
01:24:02.618 --> 01:24:05.454
Now back to sleep.

671
01:24:05.580 --> 01:24:08.206
I'll come say good night again.

672
01:24:08.499 --> 01:24:10.584
Say good night to everyone.

673
01:24:12.003 --> 01:24:14.921
The girl is completely different.

674
01:24:15.047 --> 01:24:17.883
She loves combinations of words.

675
01:24:18.050 --> 01:24:20.343
A new phrase enchants her.

676
01:24:20.720 --> 01:24:24.514
Sometimes she invents them herself.
I've written down a few.


677
01:24:24.682 --> 01:24:26.183
For example...

678
01:24:26.893 --> 01:24:29.102
"Who is the mother of the sun?"

679
01:24:30.605 --> 01:24:32.439
It's really beautiful.

680
01:24:32.565 --> 01:24:34.649
The words of a poet.

681
01:24:35.651 --> 01:24:40.197
- Do they sleep with you?
- They'd like to, but they're not allowed.


682
01:24:40.948 --> 01:24:44.326
But sometimes
the little one sneaks into our room


683
01:24:44.452 --> 01:24:48.288
and slips into our bed
between the two of us.


684
01:24:48.414 --> 01:24:51.875
He takes one of my fingers
and squeezes it tightly.


685
01:24:52.293 --> 01:24:55.545
You can't imagine
how sweet it is to fall asleep


686
01:24:55.922 --> 01:24:58.298
with a little child next to you.

687
01:25:10.061 --> 01:25:12.771
Have you known Steiner long?

688
01:25:13.105 --> 01:25:16.608
Yes, but we've only seen
each other a few times.


689
01:25:16.776 --> 01:25:18.276
But...

690
01:25:39.298 --> 01:25:43.802
Marcello, you'll have a home
like this one day too.


691
01:25:52.687 --> 01:25:55.105
We make a good pair.

692
01:25:55.273 --> 01:25:57.357
We're made for each other.

693
01:26:23.551 --> 01:26:28.054
- You have to invite me more often.
- Anytime you like.


694
01:26:28.806 --> 01:26:30.682
What is it, Marcello?

695
01:26:31.684 --> 01:26:35.770
I need a change of scene.
I need to change a lot of things.


696
01:26:38.024 --> 01:26:40.025
Your home is a refuge.

697
01:26:40.192 --> 01:26:43.862
Your children, your wife, your books,
your extraordinary friends.


698
01:26:44.447 --> 01:26:47.699
I'm wasting my life.
I'm not going anywhere.


699
01:26:47.867 --> 01:26:50.243
I had ambitions once.

700
01:26:50.369 --> 01:26:54.289
Maybe I'm losing everything,
forgetting all that.


701
01:26:54.749 --> 01:26:58.835
The answer isn't being locked up
at home. Don't do what I've done.


702
01:27:00.296 --> 01:27:02.964
I'm too serious to be an amateur,

703
01:27:03.090 --> 01:27:05.967
but not serious enough
to be a professional.


704
01:27:07.303 --> 01:27:10.680
The most miserable life is better,
believe me,


705
01:27:11.015 --> 01:27:14.392
than an existence
protected by a society


706
01:27:14.810 --> 01:27:19.356
where everything's organized
and planned for and perfect.


707
01:27:21.400 --> 01:27:25.987
I can only be a friend,
so I can't give you any advice.


708
01:27:26.656 --> 01:27:28.573
But if you like,

709
01:27:28.741 --> 01:27:32.994
I could introduce you to a publisher
who'd give you a decent job


710
01:27:33.120 --> 01:27:36.039
and a chance to focus
on your real interests.


711
01:27:36.457 --> 01:27:40.251
Better than writing
for those semifascist rags, right?


712
01:27:40.586 --> 01:27:43.630
Want to think about it
and discuss it later?


713
01:27:44.131 --> 01:27:45.382
Yes.

714
01:27:51.972 --> 01:27:53.556
Come with me.

715
01:29:04.170 --> 01:29:06.171
Sometimes at night...

716
01:29:07.131 --> 01:29:10.008
the darkness and silence
weigh on me.


717
01:29:11.552 --> 01:29:13.928
It's peace that frightens me.

718
01:29:14.221 --> 01:29:16.681
I fear peace
more than anything else.


719
01:29:16.849 --> 01:29:19.517
It seems to me it's just a facade

720
01:29:19.643 --> 01:29:22.187
with hell hiding behind it.

721
01:29:22.855 --> 01:29:26.149
I think of what my children
will see in the future.


722
01:29:26.567 --> 01:29:29.277
"It will be a wonderful world,"
they say.


723
01:29:29.403 --> 01:29:34.324
But how, when a phone call
can end it all?


724
01:29:35.576 --> 01:29:39.287
One should live
beyond passion and emotion,


725
01:29:39.413 --> 01:29:42.665
in the harmony found
in perfect works of art,


726
01:29:43.167 --> 01:29:45.543
in that enchanted order.

727
01:29:47.213 --> 01:29:50.048
We should learn
to love one another,


728
01:29:50.674 --> 01:29:54.135
to live outside of time,
detached.


729
01:29:57.431 --> 01:29:59.224
Detached.

730
01:30:08.025 --> 01:30:11.194
I can't spend my life calling you!

731
01:30:12.404 --> 01:30:15.907
I want to work in peace!
I don't know!


732
01:30:16.033 --> 01:30:18.827
Could you please
turn off that jukebox?


733
01:30:21.080 --> 01:30:25.083
No, I won't tell you where I am!
Go to hell!


734
01:30:25.292 --> 01:30:27.335
Crazy idiot!

735
01:30:47.731 --> 01:30:50.191
You think I could have some quiet?

736
01:30:51.777 --> 01:30:55.154
- This one's broken, Paola.
- Get another one.


737
01:30:55.489 --> 01:30:59.701
Are you eating here?
- No... yes... I don't know.


738
01:31:00.286 --> 01:31:02.495
The food's good, you know.

739
01:31:08.043 --> 01:31:10.503
Is it hard to learn to type?

740
01:31:11.463 --> 01:31:14.632
- You want to be a typist?
- I'd love to.


741
01:31:15.175 --> 01:31:18.928
- You're very pretty, you know?
- Oh, don't exaggerate.


742
01:31:19.847 --> 01:31:22.473
You know very well you're pretty.

743
01:31:22.641 --> 01:31:25.643
- Yeah, sure.
- This is broken.


744
01:31:25.811 --> 01:31:28.813
You're not from Rome.
Where are you from?


745
01:31:29.273 --> 01:31:33.151
- Umbria, near Perugia.
- How'd you end up here?


746
01:31:33.485 --> 01:31:35.987
My father's working in Anzio,
so I came here.


747
01:31:36.155 --> 01:31:40.116
But after Christmas
I'm moving to Ostia or Rome.


748
01:31:41.035 --> 01:31:43.953
- Who's he, your brother?
- He's my helper.


749
01:31:44.079 --> 01:31:46.497
They treat you well here!

750
01:31:46.665 --> 01:31:50.209
Yes... but I don't like it much.

751
01:31:50.544 --> 01:31:52.462
I can't wait to go home.

752
01:31:52.796 --> 01:31:56.174
Sunday I saw a car
with a Perugia license plate,


753
01:31:56.342 --> 01:31:59.052
and I felt so homesick I nearly cried.

754
01:32:01.889 --> 01:32:05.892
- Show me your profile.
- Why?


755
01:32:06.018 --> 01:32:07.936
Just for a second.

756
01:32:08.479 --> 01:32:12.565
You look like a little angel
from an Umbrian church.


757
01:32:13.025 --> 01:32:16.945
You've heard that before, huh?
Why are you laughing?


758
01:32:17.279 --> 01:32:18.655
No reason.

759
01:32:20.282 --> 01:32:24.535
- You have a boyfriend?
- Yeah, right.


760
01:32:30.960 --> 01:32:32.877
You're not writing anymore?

761
01:32:35.506 --> 01:32:38.549
Can I turn the music back on?
- Sure.


762
01:32:40.135 --> 01:32:43.012
You throwing away
this piece of paper too?


763
01:33:23.721 --> 01:33:25.013
What do you want?

764
01:33:30.936 --> 01:33:34.147
- Marcello, your father's here.
- My father?


765
01:33:34.314 --> 01:33:36.774
A guy over there
says he's your father.


766
01:33:36.942 --> 01:33:38.609
Stop joking around.

767
01:33:38.777 --> 01:33:43.573
He's eating over there.
He's been waiting for two hours.


768
01:33:43.699 --> 01:33:46.075
Didn't he say he was his father?

769
01:33:48.787 --> 01:33:52.623
He's sitting over there.
- Where?


770
01:33:52.750 --> 01:33:54.584
Next to the black guy.

771
01:34:07.431 --> 01:34:08.598
Dad.

772
01:34:14.146 --> 01:34:15.605
Finally!

773
01:34:16.148 --> 01:34:18.691
I arrived in Rome this morning.

774
01:34:18.817 --> 01:34:21.694
I looked for you at your place
and at the newspaper.


775
01:34:21.820 --> 01:34:25.615
I was about to leave
when your friend said to wait here.


776
01:34:25.741 --> 01:34:27.533
That's Paparazzo.

777
01:34:27.659 --> 01:34:32.080
I'm out and about all day for work.
I only go home to sleep.


778
01:34:32.206 --> 01:34:33.790
Why are you in Rome?

779
01:34:33.957 --> 01:34:37.668
To grease a few palms
at the ministry.


780
01:34:37.836 --> 01:34:41.005
They can cover up anything.
You look well.


781
01:34:41.131 --> 01:34:44.342
So do you. How's Mother?

782
01:34:44.718 --> 01:34:46.803
She gave me a letter for you.

783
01:34:46.970 --> 01:34:50.556
She's well.
Always worrying, as usual.


784
01:34:50.808 --> 01:34:54.227
And with age these things get worse.
Here it is.


785
01:34:55.521 --> 01:34:58.356
- Poor Mother.
- And you, dear boy...


786
01:34:58.649 --> 01:35:02.610
you could write more often,
and even come see us.


787
01:35:03.028 --> 01:35:06.239
When were you home last?
- I know, but things here...


788
01:35:08.367 --> 01:35:12.161
- She said hello. Is she an actress?
- An actress?


789
01:35:12.579 --> 01:35:16.290
She wishes!
She's a two-bit extra.


790
01:35:17.751 --> 01:35:22.421
- Dad, you want a gin fizz?
- "Gin fritz"?


791
01:35:22.548 --> 01:35:24.257
My beer is fine.

792
01:35:26.051 --> 01:35:30.596
This place is hopping at night!
Is it always like this?


793
01:35:30.722 --> 01:35:31.764
Yes.

794
01:35:31.932 --> 01:35:35.476
Back home
it's dead at this hour.


795
01:35:36.228 --> 01:35:39.689
But you're doing well here?
Have you adjusted?


796
01:35:39.857 --> 01:35:41.440
Sure, by now.

797
01:35:41.567 --> 01:35:43.734
Does your work pay well?

798
01:35:43.902 --> 01:35:47.029
Journalism pays quite well
if you're good at it.


799
01:35:47.156 --> 01:35:49.782
I'm lucky.
I've met the right people.


800
01:35:49.950 --> 01:35:52.660
I can even get into parliament
and the Vatican.


801
01:35:52.786 --> 01:35:56.372
I have a car, an apartment...
- Speaking of which...


802
01:35:56.540 --> 01:36:00.042
who's that woman
who always answers your phone?


803
01:36:00.252 --> 01:36:04.547
You're a grown man now.
Just don't do anything foolish.


804
01:36:04.673 --> 01:36:08.259
Have fun if you want,
but marriage is a serious matter.


805
01:36:08.385 --> 01:36:11.137
A woman just living with you...

806
01:36:11.305 --> 01:36:14.807
Now I understand.
You spoke with the cleaning lady.


807
01:36:16.560 --> 01:36:19.270
- So you finally found him?
- Yes, thanks.


808
01:36:19.771 --> 01:36:22.565
So you two have met?
- Sure.


809
01:36:22.733 --> 01:36:25.276
He told me to wait for you here.

810
01:36:25.652 --> 01:36:28.321
Are you a photographer?
- Yes.


811
01:36:28.488 --> 01:36:32.450
Interesting work.
Artistic, in a certain sense.


812
01:36:32.618 --> 01:36:36.621
You work with my son?
- Yeah, I got stuck with him.


813
01:36:37.331 --> 01:36:42.210
Any idea where the prince went?
I almost had him, but he got away.


814
01:36:42.336 --> 01:36:44.128
I'm gonna look for him.

815
01:36:44.254 --> 01:36:47.006
- Maybe you boys are busy?
- Not at all.


816
01:36:47.132 --> 01:36:49.926
Maybe you have an appointment...

817
01:36:50.385 --> 01:36:53.137
- My work is here too.
- Really?


818
01:36:53.680 --> 01:36:57.767
It's where you find interesting people,
or a bit of news, or a good picture.


819
01:36:57.935 --> 01:36:59.936
My paper's up there.
- I see.


820
01:37:00.479 --> 01:37:03.356
So you just sit here?

821
01:37:04.858 --> 01:37:07.568
- Shall we go to the movies?
- No.


822
01:37:07.694 --> 01:37:11.155
That's all I do at home.

823
01:37:11.531 --> 01:37:15.701
But I'll leave you alone now.

824
01:37:15.827 --> 01:37:19.121
You're young...
- No, Dad, we have nothing to do.


825
01:37:19.706 --> 01:37:25.503
What could we do this late
for a few hours before bed?


826
01:37:25.671 --> 01:37:29.298
- At this hour it's just nightclubs.
- That reminds me:


827
01:37:29.424 --> 01:37:33.177
A friend who came here
told me about a place.


828
01:37:33.303 --> 01:37:37.974
A kind of cabaret.
The Chi-Cha or Ki-Ka...


829
01:37:38.100 --> 01:37:40.184
The Cha-Cha?
That's an old one.


830
01:37:40.352 --> 01:37:42.979
- That's it! The Cha-Cha.
- You want to go there?


831
01:37:43.105 --> 01:37:46.482
Well, I suppose
we could have a look,


832
01:37:46.608 --> 01:37:49.026
since I'm here so rarely.

833
01:37:49.861 --> 01:37:53.197
Good idea!
Invite your friend. It's on me.


834
01:37:53.323 --> 01:37:57.201
No, I'll get this.
Let me handle it.


835
01:37:58.078 --> 01:38:00.621
- Antonio, come here.
- Waiter!


836
01:38:04.418 --> 01:38:07.211
- We're going with my father.
- Where?


837
01:38:07.421 --> 01:38:09.505
What about the prince?

838
01:38:09.798 --> 01:38:14.135
What? Oh, I see.
It's all lumped together here.


839
01:38:14.261 --> 01:38:16.554
Paparazzo, hurry up.

840
01:38:16.680 --> 01:38:18.222
Dad, over here.

841
01:38:20.100 --> 01:38:21.809
To the Cha
-Cha
-Cha.

842
01:38:21.935 --> 01:38:26.272
I have my Vespa here!
Take it for me, okay?


843
01:38:26.690 --> 01:38:29.525
Tell the boss
I'll call him at home.


844
01:38:29.735 --> 01:38:32.570
Get moving, boys!

845
01:38:55.761 --> 01:38:57.553
Will this table do?

846
01:38:57.679 --> 01:39:01.223
Nothing's changed!
Just like I remember it.


847
01:39:02.267 --> 01:39:07.104
Were you here in 1922?
- No, I was in Turin.


848
01:39:07.230 --> 01:39:10.191
I've only been in Rome
a few years.


849
01:39:19.618 --> 01:39:22.995
- Dad, you want a drink?
- Of course!


850
01:39:23.121 --> 01:39:26.040
- Whiskey?
- Yes, whiskey.


851
01:39:26.166 --> 01:39:27.792
Three whiskeys.

852
01:39:28.043 --> 01:39:31.128
- Very well. What label?
- Black & White.


853
01:39:31.338 --> 01:39:35.049
Why not do an article on this place?
It's like a cemetery.


854
01:39:35.175 --> 01:39:38.552
A beautiful woman!
Nice long gams.


855
01:39:38.845 --> 01:39:41.430
- What?
- He said she has long legs.


856
01:39:41.598 --> 01:39:43.641
Have you been to Paris?

857
01:39:43.809 --> 01:39:48.771
I was there a few times.
Once, in a cabaret like this,


858
01:39:48.897 --> 01:39:52.400
there was this beautiful girl,
with nice gams like that one.


859
01:39:52.526 --> 01:39:55.611
She began to strip,
and when she was naked,


860
01:39:55.987 --> 01:39:58.948
it turned out she was a he.

861
01:39:59.658 --> 01:40:02.368
Is your father still living?
- Yes.


862
01:40:02.661 --> 01:40:05.871
He must still be young.
What's he do?


863
01:40:06.164 --> 01:40:08.958
Nothing. He's a bum.
He just lazes around...


864
01:40:09.167 --> 01:40:12.128
bothering my poor mother and sister.

865
01:40:12.254 --> 01:40:15.881
He sings, whistles,
begs for money for the movies.


866
01:40:16.007 --> 01:40:18.259
It's not true.

867
01:40:51.585 --> 01:40:54.545
Paparazzo, look over there.

868
01:41:05.182 --> 01:41:08.642
- Lilly, look who's here!
- He's a looker!


869
01:41:16.735 --> 01:41:20.362
I'm still waiting to see
my picture in your paper, creep!


870
01:41:20.489 --> 01:41:22.239
You're beautiful!

871
01:41:22.407 --> 01:41:24.617
- What's her name?
- Fanny.


872
01:41:24.743 --> 01:41:27.411
- You know her well?
- You bet he does!


873
01:41:27.537 --> 01:41:30.080
- She's French.
- Very nice.


874
01:41:30.540 --> 01:41:32.208
She's French?

875
01:41:42.427 --> 01:41:44.094
Liar!

876
01:41:44.262 --> 01:41:47.097
Joker! Fibber!

877
01:41:47.432 --> 01:41:49.725
How can you stand him?

878
01:41:49.851 --> 01:41:52.603
- This is my father.
- Sure!


879
01:41:52.729 --> 01:41:54.480
- She doesn't believe me.
- Why not?


880
01:41:55.273 --> 01:41:57.650
- Really?
- Yes.


881
01:42:02.822 --> 01:42:04.907
My compliments!
You're beautiful!


882
01:42:05.075 --> 01:42:09.286
It's because I promised her a picture.
She's really very nice.


883
01:42:09.412 --> 01:42:11.372
I don't doubt it.

884
01:42:11.498 --> 01:42:13.707
- Shall we invite her over?
- Why not?


885
01:42:13.833 --> 01:42:15.709
Invite her over!

886
01:42:16.127 --> 01:42:19.505
And let's order some champagne.

887
01:42:19.631 --> 01:42:21.924
Orange soda is fine for her.

888
01:42:22.050 --> 01:42:25.928
- No, champagne is fine.
- We'll order Veuve Clicquot.


889
01:42:26.346 --> 01:42:29.598
Let me handle it.
I know about these things.


890
01:42:29.766 --> 01:42:32.101
I sold champagne to half of Italy!

891
01:42:32.644 --> 01:42:34.853
Meanwhile, here's your whiskey.

892
01:42:57.627 --> 01:42:59.837
To your health, my boy.

893
01:43:02.173 --> 01:43:04.425
- And to yours, Dad.
- Thanks.


894
01:43:09.848 --> 01:43:12.182
- It's good.
- Yes, it is.


895
01:43:19.649 --> 01:43:22.693
Did you order champagne?
Here it is.


896
01:43:22.861 --> 01:43:25.654
And it comes with a waitress!
What more could you want?


897
01:43:25.780 --> 01:43:28.032
Fanny. Don't get up.

898
01:43:28.366 --> 01:43:30.993
I'm not saying hello to you...
or you.


899
01:43:31.536 --> 01:43:35.414
Have you seen your son at work?
Some job!


900
01:43:35.707 --> 01:43:38.250
Send him back to his hometown.

901
01:43:39.085 --> 01:43:41.670
You can't really be his father.

902
01:43:41.796 --> 01:43:43.547
- I am!
- You're too young.


903
01:43:44.007 --> 01:43:47.676
Please, young lady,
let's forget about age.


904
01:43:47.802 --> 01:43:52.598
"Awaken not desperate sorrow
that presses upon my heart."


905
01:43:53.058 --> 01:43:55.934
The thing that ages us most
is boredom.


906
01:43:56.227 --> 01:43:58.937
I traveled a lot on business
as a young man,


907
01:43:59.064 --> 01:44:01.649
and I felt like a lion.

908
01:44:01.775 --> 01:44:06.737
Even now when I travel,
I can keep up with these guys.


909
01:44:06.905 --> 01:44:11.158
But when I'm at home,
I feel like I'm 80.


910
01:44:11.284 --> 01:44:15.204
What are you doing?
You take care of the Coca-Cola.


911
01:44:15.413 --> 01:44:18.082
I'll handle the champagne.

912
01:44:21.252 --> 01:44:22.628
Watch this.

913
01:44:28.802 --> 01:44:33.555
It's so beautiful.
It always makes me cry.


914
01:44:33.890 --> 01:44:36.684
That's right! it makes me cry.

915
01:45:06.798 --> 01:45:09.216
For you, young lady.

916
01:45:11.678 --> 01:45:14.221
To your beautiful legs,

917
01:45:14.347 --> 01:45:17.433
which I've had
the good fortune to admire.


918
01:46:13.698 --> 01:46:15.199
Very good.

919
01:46:15.366 --> 01:46:20.204
But now we need
another little drop.


920
01:46:22.081 --> 01:46:25.542
First I toasted
your beautiful legs.


921
01:46:26.211 --> 01:46:28.170
Now I must toast...

922
01:46:33.384 --> 01:46:36.512
I wasn't going to say
anything scandalous.


923
01:46:36.888 --> 01:46:39.264
Your father is much nicer than you.

924
01:46:39.390 --> 01:46:41.934
Much nicer!

925
01:46:42.060 --> 01:46:45.103
Don't be silly, miss.

926
01:46:45.647 --> 01:46:48.482
Listen, I'll teach you
a challenging trick.


927
01:46:48.608 --> 01:46:50.776
Let's see if you can do it.

928
01:46:50.902 --> 01:46:55.239
Watch closely.
You put a coin on your forehead,


929
01:46:55.365 --> 01:46:57.866
then make it fall
without it touching your nose.


930
01:46:57.992 --> 01:47:01.787
- That's child's play!
- Want to try?


931
01:47:01.996 --> 01:47:07.584
I'll take a coin
and put it on your forehead.


932
01:47:07.752 --> 01:47:09.920
Let's see you do it.

933
01:47:10.964 --> 01:47:13.257
- Wait.
- I'm waiting.


934
01:47:15.385 --> 01:47:16.927
Wait...

935
01:47:20.932 --> 01:47:22.933
You got me!

936
01:47:23.101 --> 01:47:26.019
Now it's my turn to tell a joke.

937
01:47:26.604 --> 01:47:30.774
A nice little story.

938
01:47:31.025 --> 01:47:35.946
A woman sends her husband
to the market


939
01:47:36.114 --> 01:47:42.619
to buy three blouses,
six handkerchiefs, and...


940
01:47:43.121 --> 01:47:45.289
What's this thing
for women called?


941
01:47:45.665 --> 01:47:47.291
A bra.

942
01:47:48.793 --> 01:47:50.836
So he sets out,

943
01:47:50.962 --> 01:47:55.090
but along the way he has some wine
and forgets everything.


944
01:47:55.216 --> 01:47:58.302
When he gets home,
the teacher asks...


945
01:47:58.428 --> 01:48:01.221
- Teacher?
- His wife.


946
01:48:01.514 --> 01:48:04.308
"Did you forget my things?"

947
01:48:04.475 --> 01:48:07.769
"No! They're right here,"
and he takes out his handkerchief.


948
01:48:07.937 --> 01:48:10.981
- "Where are my handkerchiefs?"
- "Right here.


949
01:48:11.149 --> 01:48:14.985
One, two, three, four, five, six."

950
01:48:15.111 --> 01:48:16.987
"And my blouses?"

951
01:48:17.113 --> 01:48:20.532
"Right here. One, two."

952
01:48:20.658 --> 01:48:22.993
"And where's my bra?"

953
01:48:23.202 --> 01:48:27.039
"Wait, I bought it. 
I really did...

954
01:48:27.916 --> 01:48:30.125
Here it is!"

955
01:48:31.628 --> 01:48:35.380
- But you don't need one. I like yours.
- Dad!


956
01:48:35.506 --> 01:48:37.382
She's so beautiful!

957
01:48:38.676 --> 01:48:42.387
The champagne's all gone.
We need to order more.


958
01:48:42.513 --> 01:48:44.181
Waiter!

959
01:48:49.479 --> 01:48:52.856
Hey, this is a waltz!

960
01:48:53.316 --> 01:48:55.317
I have half a mind to...

961
01:48:55.443 --> 01:48:58.487
Miss, may I have this dance?
- Here I am.


962
01:48:58.613 --> 01:49:00.280
I'm ready too.

963
01:49:02.200 --> 01:49:05.077
What's wrong? I can manage!

964
01:49:15.838 --> 01:49:20.342
You know, when I was a boy...
Paparazzo, have one.


965
01:49:20.718 --> 01:49:23.470
When I was a boy,
he was never at home.


966
01:49:23.596 --> 01:49:27.557
He'd be away weeks at a time.
He was never there.


967
01:49:28.601 --> 01:49:31.061
How my mother cried!

968
01:49:31.896 --> 01:49:36.191
I almost never saw him.
I hardly even know him.


969
01:49:38.569 --> 01:49:41.238
But I've enjoyed
seeing him again tonight.


970
01:49:42.407 --> 01:49:45.033
He's a nice guy, huh?
- Very.


971
01:49:45.159 --> 01:49:49.705
Make sure he enjoys himself tonight.
- Yes, but...


972
01:49:52.125 --> 01:49:55.502
Maybe this isn't how
you dance to this music.


973
01:49:55.628 --> 01:49:58.005
Don't worry. I like this better.

974
01:49:58.131 --> 01:50:01.091
Really? Then let's dance!

975
01:50:01.884 --> 01:50:04.594
What extraordinary eyes!
- Really?


976
01:50:04.762 --> 01:50:09.266
I'm not sure how to take that.
- As a sign of my infinite admiration.


977
01:50:09.434 --> 01:50:11.935
I fear you're just like your son.

978
01:50:12.270 --> 01:50:14.521
What? Like my son?

979
01:50:14.647 --> 01:50:17.357
We must be of the same breed!

980
01:50:22.071 --> 01:50:25.907
No! Daddy, come with me!

981
01:50:26.284 --> 01:50:29.703
Marcello, follow me.
You know where I live.


982
01:50:29.829 --> 01:50:33.665
Careful, 'cause I drive really fast,
though my car's not English!


983
01:50:34.625 --> 01:50:37.961
Dad, you're really going
to her place for spaghetti?


984
01:50:38.129 --> 01:50:41.506
