is there no electricity out here?


1226
02:10:48.129 --> 02:10:50.381
Watch out for bats!

1227
02:10:50.507 --> 02:10:53.676
Bats? They're my favorite.

1228
02:10:53.802 --> 02:10:56.887
Watch out, Nicolina.
The politician is after you.


1229
02:10:57.055 --> 02:11:00.391
Dear, the key isn't in the door.

1230
02:11:00.558 --> 02:11:03.560
It must be on the ground.
Give me some light.


1231
02:11:04.479 --> 02:11:06.647
I don't see it.

1232
02:11:08.400 --> 02:11:11.902
It's not here.
We have to go back.


1233
02:11:12.070 --> 02:11:14.905
- Here's the key.
- Give it here.


1234
02:11:15.073 --> 02:11:17.992
- Well done!
- Who found it? Nicolina?


1235
02:11:18.743 --> 02:11:22.913
- When were you last inside here?
- About two years ago.


1236
02:11:23.665 --> 02:11:27.751
I'd turn it into a great bachelor pad,
but Father says no.


1237
02:11:27.919 --> 02:11:30.254
Will you be writing an article

1238
02:11:30.380 --> 02:11:32.673
about the stupid
and corrupt aristocracy?


1239
02:11:32.841 --> 02:11:36.593
First, I write about other things.
Second, you're not that interesting.


1240
02:11:36.720 --> 02:11:39.930
Who came here with Maddalena?
- Who's Maddalena?


1241
02:11:42.058 --> 02:11:45.686
Careful. It's full of mice,
cockroaches, vipers, and vampires...


1242
02:11:45.854 --> 02:11:48.939
and now sluts.
- Thank you.


1243
02:11:51.776 --> 02:11:54.445
I'll go ahead and light the way.

1244
02:11:55.363 --> 02:11:59.575
- Giulio, when was this built?
- Five centuries ago.


1245
02:11:59.951 --> 02:12:01.910
Five centuries of love.

1246
02:12:02.078 --> 02:12:04.621
- Any popes in the family?
- Two.


1247
02:12:04.789 --> 02:12:08.375
- Countess Cristina.
- If you're scared, I'll hold you.


1248
02:12:08.501 --> 02:12:10.544
Two popes, darling!

1249
02:12:11.296 --> 02:12:13.297
I'll be your guide.

1250
02:12:13.423 --> 02:12:15.424
This way.

1251
02:12:15.800 --> 02:12:18.594
We're sweeping the floor
with our gowns.


1252
02:12:18.762 --> 02:12:22.556
- Irene, I could love you up here.
- You clown!


1253
02:12:25.643 --> 02:12:28.937
Allow me to say
you're like a beautiful apparition


1254
02:12:29.064 --> 02:12:31.315
right out of a painting.

1255
02:12:43.161 --> 02:12:45.537
What a disaster!

1256
02:12:47.040 --> 02:12:50.292
This whole room
would have to be shored up.


1257
02:12:55.507 --> 02:13:00.511
Giulio, it pains me
to see this place crumble.


1258
02:13:00.678 --> 02:13:06.100
But you're always in Rome.
You don't look after it.


1259
02:13:06.226 --> 02:13:08.227
What can I do, Dad?

1260
02:13:08.353 --> 02:13:11.271
What?
This will all be yours one day.


1261
02:13:11.398 --> 02:13:14.149
Giulio, I'm your forefather.

1262
02:13:14.275 --> 02:13:16.527
Go away, you idiot.

1263
02:13:21.366 --> 02:13:24.952
If you see a ghost,
leap into my arms.


1264
02:13:25.120 --> 02:13:26.495
All right.

1265
02:13:32.877 --> 02:13:34.378
Eugenio, stop it!

1266
02:13:35.338 --> 02:13:37.214
Otherwise go away.

1267
02:13:37.549 --> 02:13:39.466
Is your aunt a medium?

1268
02:13:39.592 --> 02:13:41.218
Didn't you know?

1269
02:13:41.386 --> 02:13:44.888
Her husband left her because
there was always a ghost in her bed.


1270
02:13:45.056 --> 02:13:46.473
I remember.

1271
02:13:47.225 --> 02:13:51.019
We've met somewhere.
I don't forget a face like that.


1272
02:13:51.146 --> 02:13:54.231
Well, I work,
so perhaps it was in some office.


1273
02:13:54.357 --> 02:13:56.400
- You work?
- Yes.


1274
02:13:57.652 --> 02:13:59.736
Who are you trying to summon?

1275
02:14:02.115 --> 02:14:04.783
- Stop fooling around.
- Cristina's making me laugh.


1276
02:14:04.909 --> 02:14:07.035
It's not true.

1277
02:14:07.871 --> 02:14:09.663
Who are you?

1278
02:14:11.291 --> 02:14:13.709
Who do you wish
to communicate with?


1279
02:14:13.835 --> 02:14:15.586
I feel an energy.

1280
02:14:15.920 --> 02:14:17.671
Keep the contact, Countess.

1281
02:14:17.797 --> 02:14:19.923
And don't laugh.
- I'm not.


1282
02:14:20.091 --> 02:14:23.093
Do you have a message
for one of us?


1283
02:14:23.470 --> 02:14:25.012
Answer, please.

1284
02:14:25.638 --> 02:14:30.767
What's that light down there
blinking on and off?


1285
02:14:30.935 --> 02:14:33.020
Don't be scared.
It's a tractor.


1286
02:14:33.146 --> 02:14:35.606
In summer they work at night too.

1287
02:14:38.067 --> 02:14:40.694
- Call Sister Edvige.
- Who's she?


1288
02:14:40.862 --> 02:14:44.948
A nun who walks around
with her head on a plate.


1289
02:14:45.116 --> 02:14:46.575
Don't be stupid.

1290
02:14:47.577 --> 02:14:51.747
Is it you again?
Who won't you leave me alone?


1291
02:14:52.081 --> 02:14:54.249
Please go away!

1292
02:14:55.585 --> 02:14:57.836
Ask if it's the same woman
as last time.


1293
02:14:57.962 --> 02:15:00.839
The scent
of your breath in my lungs


1294
02:15:00.965 --> 02:15:03.425
and your blood in my veins!

1295
02:15:06.471 --> 02:15:08.555
She's just drunk.

1296
02:15:14.687 --> 02:15:16.647
Why's she doing that?

1297
02:15:17.815 --> 02:15:19.942
Blow out the candles!

1298
02:15:21.277 --> 02:15:23.320
Blow them out!

1299
02:15:29.160 --> 02:15:32.079
Who are you?
Tell me who you are.


1300
02:15:35.833 --> 02:15:38.335
Who do you wish
to communicate with?


1301
02:15:39.337 --> 02:15:41.046
Giulio?

1302
02:15:41.172 --> 02:15:44.007
Giulio, there's a message for you.

1303
02:15:44.801 --> 02:15:47.678
That slut is in love with you.

1304
02:15:48.513 --> 02:15:51.723
Giulio, you can't run from my love.

1305
02:15:53.518 --> 02:15:57.854
- Enough! Let's have some light!
- We're just joking around.


1306
02:15:58.356 --> 02:16:00.524
Irene, come here.

1307
02:16:04.904 --> 02:16:06.989
Who are you, poor soul?

1308
02:16:07.865 --> 02:16:09.741
Why are you crying?

1309
02:16:13.454 --> 02:16:15.289
Why are you crying?

1310
02:16:24.799 --> 02:16:26.717
Wait, I'll light a match.

1311
02:16:47.447 --> 02:16:49.239
No, not here.

1312
02:16:49.407 --> 02:16:51.617
What are you doing?

1313
02:16:51.993 --> 02:16:54.995
You're crazy, darling!

1314
02:17:11.095 --> 02:17:14.222
This is the first time
I've seen the dawn.


1315
02:17:30.865 --> 02:17:33.325
Marcello, have you met my son?

1316
02:17:34.369 --> 02:17:36.161
Pleased to meet you.

1317
02:17:40.750 --> 02:17:44.461
Shall we go have some spaghetti?

1318
02:17:50.134 --> 02:17:53.762
One egg for 45 lira?
Forget it.


1319
02:17:53.888 --> 02:17:56.473
We'll buy them in Capranica.

1320
02:17:59.852 --> 02:18:01.812
Still out and about at this hour?

1321
02:18:02.480 --> 02:18:04.564
Good morning.

1322
02:18:08.653 --> 02:18:12.656
- Did you sleep well, Mother?
- Think you're still a young thing?


1323
02:18:13.324 --> 02:18:15.826
We went up to the old villa.

1324
02:18:15.952 --> 02:18:18.662
Is crazy Francesca with you?

1325
02:18:19.330 --> 02:18:22.666
- Who's she?
- The princess mother.


1326
02:18:35.513 --> 02:18:39.141
What have I done
to be treated this way?


1327
02:18:39.559 --> 02:18:42.185
Even dogs aren't treated like this!

1328
02:18:42.353 --> 02:18:44.312
Who do you think you are?

1329
02:18:46.649 --> 02:18:51.319
If you loved me half as much
as I love you, you'd understand.


1330
02:18:51.487 --> 02:18:52.696
Sure.

1331
02:18:52.864 --> 02:18:56.366
- But you don't love anyone!
- Stop shouting.


1332
02:18:56.534 --> 02:19:01.288
- You don't know what love is!
- And I suppose you do.


1333
02:19:01.414 --> 02:19:05.333
Your heart is closed and empty.

1334
02:19:05.460 --> 02:19:09.296
All you think about is women...
and you think that's love!


1335
02:19:09.422 --> 02:19:12.215
You've been saying that
for four hours.


1336
02:19:12.383 --> 02:19:15.844
I've heard enough!
I want to go home!


1337
02:19:16.387 --> 02:19:19.723
Some men are happy to find
someone who loves them.


1338
02:19:19.891 --> 02:19:22.559
They don't go running
after other women.


1339
02:19:22.685 --> 02:19:25.145
You're the only one like this!

1340
02:19:25.271 --> 02:19:27.981
It's a disgrace!

1341
02:19:28.149 --> 02:19:32.402
My disgrace is having met you!

1342
02:19:32.737 --> 02:19:34.237
Understand?

1343
02:19:34.363 --> 02:19:36.490
I can't stand being around you!

1344
02:19:36.866 --> 02:19:38.408
Go away!

1345
02:19:38.618 --> 02:19:41.411
Go away and never come back!

1346
02:19:47.084 --> 02:19:49.836
Where are you going, stupid?
Come back.


1347
02:19:50.046 --> 02:19:53.215
Leave me alone!
Let me live my life!


1348
02:20:01.015 --> 02:20:03.600
Get in the car, you idiot!

1349
02:20:05.561 --> 02:20:07.562
Look, Emma, I'll...

1350
02:20:13.861 --> 02:20:15.111
Get in.

1351
02:20:16.280 --> 02:20:19.241
What do you want from me?

1352
02:20:20.576 --> 02:20:23.119
You're a miserable worm!

1353
02:20:23.496 --> 02:20:26.289
You'll end up all alone like a dog!

1354
02:20:28.167 --> 02:20:29.876
You'll see.

1355
02:20:30.294 --> 02:20:33.630
Who'll stay with you
if I leave you?


1356
02:20:36.300 --> 02:20:39.219
What will you do with your life?

1357
02:20:39.345 --> 02:20:41.471
No one will love you like I do.

1358
02:20:41.764 --> 02:20:45.058
I can't spend my life loving you.

1359
02:20:45.434 --> 02:20:47.853
You say I'm the crazy one,

1360
02:20:47.979 --> 02:20:51.356
living in a dream,
out of touch with reality.


1361
02:20:52.149 --> 02:20:55.318
But it's you
who's got it all wrong.


1362
02:20:55.945 --> 02:20:59.990
Can't you see you already have
the most important thing in life?


1363
02:21:00.199 --> 02:21:05.745
A woman who really loves you,
who'd give her life for you.


1364
02:21:06.956 --> 02:21:08.957
But you spoil everything.

1365
02:21:09.375 --> 02:21:13.169
You're always restless, unhappy.

1366
02:21:20.011 --> 02:21:24.306
When two people love each other,
nothing else matters.


1367
02:21:24.807 --> 02:21:27.017
What are you afraid of?

1368
02:21:27.977 --> 02:21:30.687
Of you... your selfishness...

1369
02:21:30.855 --> 02:21:33.023
your miserable ideals.

1370
02:21:33.274 --> 02:21:36.067
You offer me a life
fit for a worm.


1371
02:21:36.193 --> 02:21:38.695
You only talk of cooking and bed.

1372
02:21:38.863 --> 02:21:42.198
A man who lives like that
is done for!


1373
02:21:42.325 --> 02:21:44.367
He's nothing but a worm!

1374
02:21:44.952 --> 02:21:49.331
I don't believe in your aggressive,
clinging, maternal love!


1375
02:21:49.498 --> 02:21:51.875
I don't want it!
I don't need it!


1376
02:21:52.335 --> 02:21:55.086
That's not love, it's degradation!

1377
02:21:55.504 --> 02:21:57.714
I can't live like this!

1378
02:21:57.882 --> 02:22:01.051
I don't want to be
with you anymore!


1379
02:22:01.218 --> 02:22:03.553
Get out!
- No!


1380
02:22:03.721 --> 02:22:06.681
You're a swine, a coward!
I feel sorry for you!


1381
02:22:07.099 --> 02:22:09.976
And you make me sick!
Get out!


1382
02:22:10.394 --> 02:22:13.188
No! I'm staying here with you.

1383
02:22:13.397 --> 02:22:16.566
No, you're not. Get out.

1384
02:22:25.743 --> 02:22:27.410
Get out of the car.

1385
02:22:27.745 --> 02:22:30.538
Get out of the car! It's over!

1386
02:22:32.500 --> 02:22:35.293
It's over! Get lost!

1387
02:22:35.920 --> 02:22:37.545
Bastard!

1388
02:22:37.755 --> 02:22:40.548
You're a bastard!
A louse!


1389
02:22:41.926 --> 02:22:44.928
Damn you!
- I never want to see you again!


1390
02:22:46.180 --> 02:22:49.057
Hitch a ride with a trucker,
you slut!


1391
02:22:49.225 --> 02:22:51.184
Run off to your whores!

1392
02:23:59.003 --> 02:24:00.420
Hello.

1393
02:24:04.341 --> 02:24:05.842
Where?

1394
02:24:14.518 --> 02:24:16.603
You can't go past here.

1395
02:24:17.021 --> 02:24:18.521
Go ahead.

1396
02:24:19.523 --> 02:24:22.192
Let him through!

1397
02:24:26.197 --> 02:24:29.866
- It's just awful, Marcello.
- What happened?


1398
02:24:31.660 --> 02:24:32.786
Tiziano!

1399
02:24:33.329 --> 02:24:36.706
He shot his two children
and then killed himself.


1400
02:24:44.215 --> 02:24:46.716
Marcello, get me inside.

1401
02:24:47.218 --> 02:24:49.886
I'll give your paper the pictures.

1402
02:24:50.137 --> 02:24:52.972
Get me inside.

1403
02:24:53.140 --> 02:24:56.059
- I'm a friend. I have to come in.
- One moment.


1404
02:24:57.728 --> 02:25:01.022
Inspector, a man here says
he's a friend of Steiner's.


1405
02:25:01.190 --> 02:25:02.398
Let him in.

1406
02:25:04.860 --> 02:25:07.195
Just him, just him.

1407
02:25:10.991 --> 02:25:12.826
Come in.

1408
02:25:16.080 --> 02:25:19.165
From floor to bullet hole:
five feet.


1409
02:25:21.919 --> 02:25:25.380
Left wall to bullet hole:

1410
02:25:28.884 --> 02:25:32.762
No, the wife doesn't know yet.
She'll be back at 1:00.


1411
02:25:34.431 --> 02:25:37.183
It seems he first called a friend

1412
02:25:37.309 --> 02:25:42.438
and begged her
to meet his wife at the bus stop.


1413
02:25:42.565 --> 02:25:46.609
Rear wall to bullet hole:

1414
02:25:48.946 --> 02:25:51.447
Let's hear that again.
Rewind it.


1415
02:25:57.288 --> 02:25:59.831
You're the true primitive,

1416
02:25:59.999 --> 02:26:02.333
primitive like a gothic spire.

1417
02:26:02.459 --> 02:26:04.669
You're so tall

1418
02:26:04.795 --> 02:26:07.380
that no voices
can reach you up there.


1419
02:26:07.548 --> 02:26:10.466
Really? If you could see
my real height,


1420
02:26:10.634 --> 02:26:12.969
you'd see I'm no taller than this.

1421
02:26:15.764 --> 02:26:18.683
Were you a friend of the family?

1422
02:26:18.809 --> 02:26:20.810
I was a friend of Steiner's.

1423
02:26:21.312 --> 02:26:25.231
- For how long? Were you close?
- Had you seen him recently?


1424
02:26:25.399 --> 02:26:27.442
Could you tell us about him?

1425
02:26:28.068 --> 02:26:32.697
No. I was his friend,
but we didn't see each other often.


1426
02:26:32.823 --> 02:26:34.657
I know nothing.

1427
02:26:36.869 --> 02:26:38.328
Nothing at all.

1428
02:26:40.080 --> 02:26:42.373
Ten feet.

1429
02:26:42.750 --> 02:26:44.584
Foggia.

1430
02:26:50.174 --> 02:26:54.636
Was anything unusual
going on in his life?


1431
02:26:54.845 --> 02:26:57.639
Financial problems,
anything like that?


1432
02:26:57.765 --> 02:26:59.682
I don't think so.

1433
02:27:00.100 --> 02:27:02.727
Had he ever shown
suicidal tendencies?


1434
02:27:04.521 --> 02:27:05.855
I don't know.

1435
02:27:06.023 --> 02:27:09.108
All right.
Please remain at our disposal.


1436
02:27:09.443 --> 02:27:11.569
Mondini, get the gun.

1437
02:27:11.695 --> 02:27:16.532
He was a cheerful man
who adored his family.


1438
02:27:17.284 --> 02:27:20.870
His was
an almost morbid adoration.


1439
02:27:25.417 --> 02:27:29.879
The weapon used
was a new Browning .675.


1440
02:27:30.005 --> 02:27:32.966
It was found beside his body,

1441
02:27:33.092 --> 02:27:36.219
which was seated
in an armchair near the fireplace


1442
02:27:36.387 --> 02:27:38.554
in an unusual position.

1443
02:27:47.064 --> 02:27:49.399
I'm finished here.
I'll continue at the morgue.


1444
02:27:49.733 --> 02:27:51.484
Fine, thanks.

1445
02:27:52.236 --> 02:27:55.196
- Can we cover the body, sir?
- Yes.


1446
02:27:55.656 --> 02:27:56.781
De Angelis?

1447
02:28:04.081 --> 02:28:06.541
Did you get pictures
of everything here?


1448
02:28:06.667 --> 02:28:09.335
Then let's go to the children's room.

1449
02:28:09.461 --> 02:28:11.087
This way.

1450
02:28:12.756 --> 02:28:17.385
It's time I went down
and met his wife at the bus stop.


1451
02:28:17.928 --> 02:28:21.347
I'll take someone from the building,
because I don't know her.


1452
02:28:21.849 --> 02:28:23.975
- I'll come.
- Thank you.


1453
02:28:25.269 --> 02:28:26.769
Let's go.

1454
02:28:26.895 --> 02:28:29.314
Come down to the bus stop
when you're finished.


1455
02:28:29.440 --> 02:28:32.942
If anyone from the station comes,
call me at the office.


1456
02:29:01.638 --> 02:29:05.391
Boys, a little compassion, please,
just this once.


1457
02:29:05.851 --> 02:29:09.979
Tell your colleagues.
This is going too far.


1458
02:29:20.449 --> 02:29:22.909
Maybe he was just afraid.

1459
02:29:24.161 --> 02:29:25.995
You mean Steiner?

1460
02:29:26.163 --> 02:29:28.247
Had someone threatened him?

1461
02:29:28.374 --> 02:29:31.167
No, not in the way you mean.

1462
02:29:32.002 --> 02:29:34.587
Maybe he was afraid of himself...

1463
02:29:35.506 --> 02:29:37.215
of us all.

1464
02:29:38.884 --> 02:29:40.760
When's the bus due?

1465
02:30:06.703 --> 02:30:08.329
That's her.

1466
02:30:09.623 --> 02:30:11.499
Please come with me.

1467
02:30:20.300 --> 02:30:23.719
What's going on?
Do you think I'm an actress?


1468
02:30:24.304 --> 02:30:26.222
What are you doing?

1469
02:30:26.557 --> 02:30:29.308
What do you want?
- Stop it! Get lost!


1470
02:30:29.435 --> 02:30:31.060
Marcello, what's going on?

1471
02:30:31.228 --> 02:30:34.981
I'm Mr. Lucenti.
I must speak with you a moment.


